Present law authorizes retirees of the Teachers' Retirement System of La. to be reemployed
in a position covered by the system without a reduction of his retirement benefit if his
earnings from such employment during a fiscal year do not exceed 25% of his final average
compensation. If his earnings exceed this limit, present law authorizes him to choose a
benefit reduction or to become a member of the system again and earn a supplemental
benefit.
Proposed law retains present law except to increase the earnings limit to 100% of the
retiree's final average compensation.
Present law provides that a retiree who returns to active service within 12 months of his
retirement has his benefit suspended for the duration of reemployment or a lapse of 12
months, whichever occurs first.
Proposed law shortens the suspension duration to three months. Otherwise retains present
law.
Proposed law requires that any cost of proposed law be funded with additional employer
contributions in compliance with present constitution (Art. X, Sec. 29(F)).
(Amends R.S. 11:710.1(A)(1)(a) and (c) and (C)(1))
